title: Outrageous Dr Teleny's Incredible Plugged-In Orchestra - Stolen
description:
Outrageous Dr Teleny's Incredible Plugged-In Orchestra - Stolen Goods, Gems Lifted from the Masters (1972 quad/surround mix 24/96 lossless 4.0 DVD-A)

24/96 4.0 lossless MLP (DVD-Audio).
16/48 4.0 DTS @ 1536kbps (DVD-Video) for compatibility with standard DVD players.

Converted from quad CD-4 vinyl using an AUDIO TECHNICA AT20SLa CD-4 cartridge / JVC 4DD-5 demodulator.
 
 
Note: Easy listening "Pop" versions of classical works using modern instruments (lots of horns and the occational moog synthesizer) released on the RCA Red classical label. 

It was only released in quad, and AFAIK has never been released on CD. 

Tracks:
01 The People, Yes (Chopin - Revolutionary Etude)
02 Ludwig's Gig (Beethoven - Pastoral Symphony)
03 Wild Turkey (Mozart - Turkish Rondo
04 Rhapsody from Hunger (Liszt - Hungarian Rhapsody No.2)
05 Schubert and Stripes Forever (Schubert - Marche militaire)
06 Superioy (Bach - Jesu, Joy of Man's Desiring)
07 Johann Sebastian Rock (Bach - Sleepers, Wake)
08 Wolfgang Wigs Out (Mozart - Sonata in C: 1st Movement)
09 Power Play (Chopin - Polonaise militaire)
10 King of Kings (Handel - Messiah: Hallelujah Chorus)

Zack Laurence, Music Director.
Produced by Ken Howard and Alan Blaikley
